Privacy Policy for Swipy

Effective date: March 23, 2025

At Swipy, we value your privacy and are committed to protecting your personal information. This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, and share information when you use our application, Swipy, which is available on iOS.

1. Information We Collect

We do not collect any personally identifiable information directly through the Swipy app. However, there are certain types of information that may be collected automatically as a result of using the app:
	•	Usage Data: This may include information about how you interact with the app, such as the photos you view, how often you use the app, and how long you stay on particular screens.
	•	Device Information: This may include information about your device, such as device type, operating system version, and unique device identifiers.

2. Third-Party Services

Swipy integrates with third-party services, which may collect data about you. These third parties include:
	•	Unsplash API: Swipy fetches random photos from Unsplash API. Unsplash may collect usage data as part of their service. Please refer to Unsplash’s privacy policy for more details on how they handle user data. Unsplash Privacy Policy.

3. Use of Data

We use the data collected for the following purposes:
	•	To provide you with the photos and content you request.
	•	To improve the functionality and performance of the Swipy app.
	•	To analyze how users interact with the app to enhance user experience.

4. Data Security

We take reasonable precautions to protect your information. However, please be aware that no method of transmitting or storing data is 100% secure. While we strive to protect your personal information, we cannot guarantee its absolute security.

5. Sharing Your Information

We do not share your personal information with third parties except for the services mentioned above, such as the Unsplash API. We will not sell, trade, or rent your personal information to third parties.

6. Your Rights

Depending on your jurisdiction, you may have certain rights regarding your personal data. If you would like to know more about how we handle your information or wish to request access, correction, or deletion of your data, please contact us at [contact email].

7. Changes to This Privacy Policy

We reserve the right to update or change this Privacy Policy at any time. We will notify you of any changes by posting the updated Privacy Policy within the app. Please check this page periodically for updates.

8. Contact Us

If you have any questions about this Privacy Policy or how your information is handled, please contact us at [contact email].
